review_blob: Pours a dark brown body with a thin beige head. Aroma of roasted malts. Rich malty taste with roasted tones of bread, tree and coffee.
Pours a hazy golden body with a medium head. Nice yeasty aroma. Nice and creamy taste with malty tones and well balanced sweetness.
Pours a golden body with a medium head. Nice funky aroma. Hoppy taste with a nice funk and tones of grass and barnyard.

Pours a dark body with a thick beige head. Malty aroma of dried fruit and burnt candy. Very nice taste rich of malty flavours like toffe, dried fruit and sweet bread but still with mellow creamy feel. Very nice nice and easy for a quadruple.
Pours a purple body with a medium pink head. Nice aroma of funky cherries. The taste is a bit sour, full of cherries and medium bodies. Very nice and well balanced, easy drinking.

Pours a golden body with a thin head. Faint aroma with a hint of hops. Flat but quite nice taste with a subtle bitterness and a rather nice balance. Better than expected and would do very nice on a summer day :)
Pours a dark body with a thin beige head. Faint malty aroma. Creamy taste with malty tones of sugars and fruits.
Pours an amber body with a thin head. Faint hoppy aroma. Nice taste of malt even if it is a bit watery. Very nice subtle bitterness.
Pours a little hazy golden body with a thin head. Nice malty aroma. Well balanced creamy taste with a clear wheat character.
Pours a dark body with a thin beige head. Faint aroma of sugary candy. Rich an creamy taste will all sorts of malty flavours and some spicy notes.
beer_name: Dieu du Ciel Rigor Mortis Abt

review_blob: Pours an amber body with a medium head. Hoppy aroma with a sweet bottom. Nice hoppy taste with a somewhat creamy feel.
Pours a coffee like body with a thin head. Rich aroma of malt and barrels. Rich and full taste of malty flavours like bread, wood and fried fruit.
Pours a hazy amber body with a medium head. Nice hoppy aroma. Bitter taste of hops that is a bit off balance.
Pours a clear amber body with a medium head. Nice, strong aroma with yeasty tones. Full, somewhat creamy taste with malty flavours and a faint bitterness. Nice but a bit off balance.
Pours an amber body with a medium head. Nice sour aroma with a hint of fruit. Nice rich taste with a very well balanced sourness and a fruity touch.
Pours a hazy pale golden body with a medium head. Fruity aroma of hops. Taste is nice, a bite creamy and full of hoppy flavors.
Pours a clear amber body with a thin head. Faint hoppy aroma. Nice and round malty taste which could have been a bit richer.
Pours a dark body with a medium beige head. Faint aroma of dried fruit. Rich taste with tones of fruit, sugars and a smokey touch.

Pours a deep golden body with a medium head. Nice aroma of malty sugars and a touch of yeasty esters. The same goes for the taste which is dominated by yeasty esters with a nice malty background to back things up. A very nice and well balanced trippel.
Pours a clear amber body with a large head. Yeasty aroma with tones of sugary honey. Honey also dominates the taste in a nice way and balances well with yeasty esters.
Pours an amber body with a medium head. Sour aroma with a little fruit. Taste is fruity sour and very dry. Nice and interesting beer.
Pours a hazy golden body with a medium head. Strong hoppy aroma of flowers. Nice and fresh taste with tones of flowers, grass and hay. The hops is a bit too dominant though.
Pours an amber body with a medium head. Nice hoppy aroma. Taste is rather flat but still nice and would be a very nice refreshment in a hot summer day.
Pours a hazy golden body with a thick and lasting head. Nice aroma of funky hay. Nice and fresh taste with a nice carboration and a hint of honey.
Pours an amberish body with a medium head. Aroma of funky grass. Nice creamy touch but the taste lacks character.
Pours a deep amber body with a thin head. Rather unpleasant aroma with a hint of fruit. Taste is quite flat with a nice fruityness.
Pours a brown body with a medium head. Syrup-like aroma. Rich sugary taste with a nice creamy feel.
beer_name: Smuttynose Really Old Brown Dog Ale (2009-)

review_blob: Pours a pale amber body with a large and lasting head. Hoppy aroma. Nice and creamy taste with a well balanced funk. A very nice saison.

Pours an amber body with a medium head. Fruity aroma. Taste is a bit weird for a beer, it is probably the fig juice. It isnt bad in any way, just not whats expected. The taste does however go very well with the rest of the beer and balances well. In other word, interesting :)

Pours a hazy amber body with a medium head. Nice and rich aroma. Taste if rather rich and very well balanced. A quite nice tripel with a distinctive character. If it were belgian, it would probably be famous :)

Pours a hazy amber body with a thick and lasting head. Nice aroma of yeast and hops. Nice creamy taste, really easy drinking. Nothing out of the ordinary but still a very nice and friendly beer with a nice character from the hops which gives it personality.
Pours a hazy amber body with a thick head. Aroma a bit more herby than expected of a saison. Very nice and creamy taste which lays perfect on my tongue. One of the better saisons Ive had.
